headline: Why Chipotle (CMG) Shares Are Trading Lower Today
summary: Shares of mexican fast-food chain Chipotle (NYSE:CMG) fell 3.4% in the afternoon session after the major indices pulled back (Nasdaq -0.8%, S&P 500 -0.77%), largely due to escalating concerns surrounding the July 9th deadline for new US tariffs, now amplified by specific announcements.
